/*
 *
 * Just another raymarched SDF that I spent way too much time on.
 * Press 1, 2 or 3 to change the weather.
 *
 * List of features:
 * 
 * - Approximate line-segment lights
 * - Physically-based metallic/roughness materials
 * - Glossy reflections
 * - Procedural volumetric clouds
 * - Soft-shadows
 * - Ambient occlusion
 * - Temporal AA
 *
 * Some of the lighting math is probably wrong. I have included references and links to papers
 * and articles so if you are trying to reimplement something in your own renderer it'd be prudent to double check there.
 * The code is mostly well-commented but even where it isn't I have tried to keep it as clean and readable as possible.
 * Some things have been butchered to keep compile times down and might be hard to parse, apologies for that :(
 *
 * Thanks to everyone making so much cool stuff and publishing it for us all to learn from.
 * A lot of ideas and code have been borrowed from other shaders on this site and it has been
 * immensely helpful. Special thanks to Inigo Quilez for all the articles and code.
 * 
 * Incomplete list of techniques used in making this:
 *
 * - Cook-Torrance lighting model
 * Joey de Vries, https://learnopengl.com/PBR/Theory
 *
 * - SDFs for various shapes by Inigo Quilez
 * https://iquilezles.org/articles/distfunctions
 * https://www.shadertoy.com/view/Xds3zN
